- RULER NIAH task pattern by NVIDIA, Apache License, Version 2.0
  (algorithmic pattern only).
  Source: https://github.com/NVIDIA/RULER (paper: arXiv:2404.06654)
  The shipped ruler_32k.jsonl items (present in served suite releases as a
  zero-weight legacy item set) are LOCALLY GENERATED synthetic data — no
  upstream RULER code, prompts, or haystack data are vendored — so this is
  attribution of the algorithmic pattern, not redistribution.

- Berkeley Function-Calling Leaderboard (BFCL) by Gorilla LLM / UC Berkeley,
  distributed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (dataset and eval code).
  Dataset:   https://huggingface.co/datasets/gorilla-llm/Berkeley-Function-Calling-Leaderboard
             (revision 61fc0608cfd831fcfbbaa676ebdfef0ed963eeda)
  Eval repo: https://github.com/ShishirPatil/gorilla
             (revision 6ea57973c7a6097fd7c5915698c54c17c5b1b6c8)
  BFCL-derived items form the backbone of the tc_json_v1 tool-calling item
  set, and 100 multi-turn rows are vendored from the eval repo into
  suite/v1/bfcl_multi_turn.jsonl. Changes were made (sub-sampling,
  reformatting, and locally authored conformance items).

- LiveCodeBench (test_generation subset, contest window
  2023-12-01..2024-03-02), used for the lcb output-prediction coding items
  (lcb.jsonl remains present in served suite releases as a zero-weight
  legacy item set).
  Dataset: https://huggingface.co/datasets/livecodebench/test_generation
           (revision 6f3ac40bbecf81eba15899139d279b077f2816fd)
  The upstream Hugging Face card's license metadata is the generic "cc"
  (Creative Commons) tag; the LiveCodeBench project distributes under
  CC-BY-4.0, and this project honors CC-BY-4.0 attribution obligations:
  credit to LiveCodeBench, https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/,
  and notice that changes were made (the suite sub-samples and reformats).
  Full text: LICENSES/LiveCodeBench-CC-BY-4.0.txt.
  ADDITIONAL CAVEAT: problem statements originate from LeetCode, and LeetCode
  Terms of Service may apply to the underlying problem text; suite releases
  flag lcb.jsonl accordingly rather than treating redistribution terms as
  fully settled.

- AppWorld by StonyBrookNLP, used for the headline agentic axis (appworld_c).
  Source: https://github.com/StonyBrookNLP/appworld
  NO AppWorld data is redistributed by this project: suite releases contain
  no appworld item files; the AppWorld environment and its task data are
  fetched from upstream on the user's machine at appliance provisioning time;
  and submission bundles carry only per-task verdicts and hashes (no task
  content, empty requests, no response text) for agentic items.
  Upstream license: Apache License, Version 2.0, WITH an upstream rider that
  public redistribution of the protected task-data portion (or derivatives)
  must be in encrypted form. This project's no-redistribution posture
  complies with that rider by construction.


